HEADWORD: Weatherboarding
<hw>Weath"er*board`ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The covering or siding of a building, formed of boards
lapping over one another, to exclude rain, snow, etc.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Boards adapted or intended for such use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weather-bound</ent>⟦br⟧
